datatypes:
dynamic type language.
Two types:
1)	primitive datatype
2)	non-primitive datatype
primitive datatype: predefined,; we can store single values
1)	numbers: integers, floats   (ex: 1,-1,3.5…….)
2)	String : stream of characters  enclosed in quotes
--single, double, backtick quotes;
single, double works same;
back ticks introduced in ES6 version
it provides extra functionality ; we can insert variables into them
      3)   Boolean : true or false
      4)  empty values
     5)  undefined: declare variable with no value

